-- Global Week Ahead Calendar for Dec. 26 to Jan. 1, 2012
-- B y   G r e g   M i l e s ,   S t e p h e n   F o x w e l l   a n d   K o h   K e a t   K i a n
-- 2011-12-26T05:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-26/global-week-ahead-calendar-for-dec-26-to-jan-1-2012.html
German Chancellor  Angela Merkel  and
French President Nicolas Sarkozy may tell citizens of Europe’s
two largest countries to brace for budget cuts. Spain will
announce emergency spending reductions as Italy sells debt amid
concern it’s slipping into a recession. The  European Central
Bank  releases results of a program to mop up 211 billion euros
of market liquidity to head off inflation.  China’s manufacturing will probably shrink for the second
straight month. Japanese Prime Minister Yoshihiko Noda’s talks
in China with Premier Wen Jiabao may focus on regional security
following the death of North Korean leader  Kim Jong Il .  U.S. consumer confidence may improve as the pace of home-
price declines slows in the world’s biggest economy.  MONDAY, Dec. 26  To contact the reporters on this story:
